<p>I am an (incoming) post-doctoral scholar at Brown University, working under the supervision of Chris Horvat.</p>

<p>Prior to starting my post-doc, I earned at PhD from the School of Oceanography and the Applied Physics Lab at the University of Washington under the joint supervision of <a href="http://apl.uw.edu/people/profile.php?last_name=Rainville&amp;first_name=Luc" target="blank">Luc Rainville</a> and <a href="http://apl.uw.edu/people/profile.php?last_name=Thomson&amp;first_name=Jim" target="blank">Jim Thomson</a>. I also completed a Masterâ€™s of Applied Science degree (MASc) in Civil Engineering at the University of British Columbia, where I worked with <a href="https://www.civil.ubc.ca/faculty/bernard-laval" target="blank">Bernard Laval</a>.</p>

<p>I study the interactions of sea ice with the upper ocean as part of the <a href="https://polar-oceans.com/" target="blank"><em>Antipodal Oceanography Group</em></a>.</p>
